    "title": "1996 Fractals Calendar",
    "text": "1996 About the cover: The thin, winding curve that dances in this image captivates its surroundings. The rhythm of the repeated transformations eventually pulls all points near the curve. The colors in this image are chosen to highlight this process of captivation and the texture, reminiscent of clouds, recalls the fractal geometry of nature. I edited the 1996 Fractals calendar as a Ph.D. student at Simon Fraser University. The calendar featured images from: Robby Alyn Berry, Brian Evans, Michael Field, Martin Golubitsky, Daryl H. Hepting, F. Kenton Musgrave, Kevin Suffern, and Eric Tosan. Thanks also to: Joelle Thollot. This calendar was completed with the assistance of the Centre for Experimental and Constructive Mathematics and the Graphics and Multimedia Research Laboratory at Simon Fraser University. Earlier work was done at the University of Regina and at the IBM Thomas J. Watson Research Center. There are many to whom I continue to be grateful, but especially B. Mandelbrot, K. Musgrave, P. Prusinkiewicz, D. Saupe, and R. Voss. January: Glacial Pageant by Daryl H. Hepting February: Twisted Symmetries by Michael Field and Martin Golubitsky March: Marian Ammonite by Brian Evans April: Slickrock I.V by F. Kenton Musgrave May: Construction Zone by Daryl H. Hepting June: Beanstalks by Robby Alyn Berry July: Glory by Kevin Suffern August: Square Chaos by Michael Field and Martin Golubitsky September: Tangled Necklace by Daryl H. Hepting October: Blue October by Eric Tosan November: Pleiades III by F. Kenton Musgrave December: Captivating Rhythm by Daryl H. Hepting",
